{"id": "1420685957350293675", "channel_id": "1420653274415235094", "type": 19, "author_id": "244028747999608832", "author_name": "vxvendetta", "author_bot": false, "content": "can you give some insight on the Tinct uses? i'm interested to know", "timestamp": "2025-09-25T08:18:47.301000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": ["845527584157597716"], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": "1420653274415235094", "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1420653274415235094", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "Tier List & Banner Guide", "forum_channel_id": "1304022827824844842", "thread_tags": ["1395992270880243753", "1304022948000043028"]}
{"id": "1420861801024852121", "channel_id": "1420653274415235094", "type": 19, "author_id": "845527584157597716", "author_name": "lurenjiao", "author_bot": false, "content": "She’s mainly for increasing Crit Rate and Crit Damage, and the EX cost reduction can be handy in some cases.  Just to mention, Distant Melo affects all four teammates, so its value in Aepuor is very high.（It’s equivalent to the tentacles receiving a fourfold buff.） She is also often included in Kathigu-Ra’s team now, since Kathigu-Ra can equip The Last Verse, The Land of Nonexistence, and Feast from Afar (this setup gives her great survivability, while her damage relies on stacking fire repeatedly until a certain turn for a big burst). If Kathigu-Ra is equipped this way, her Crit Rate becomes very scarce, which makes Tinct a great teammate for Kathigu-Ra.", "timestamp": "2025-09-25T19:57:31.700000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": ["244028747999608832"], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": "1420685957350293675", "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1420653274415235094", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "Tier List & Banner Guide", "forum_channel_id": "1304022827824844842", "thread_tags": ["1395992270880243753", "1304022948000043028"]}
{"id": "1420863728319987924", "channel_id": "1420653274415235094", "type": 19, "author_id": "244028747999608832", "author_name": "vxvendetta", "author_bot": false, "content": "yeah, in that team the set up capabilities of tintc are for sure more effective.\nFor the tentacle stuff, yeah is good to get general tentacle buffs, but because the crit and crit damage buff during battle are calculated with 1\\4 of team total, so a 45% crit rate buff for the team is 45% buff for the tentacle in general.\nBut there are other teams that can use her well?", "timestamp": "2025-09-25T20:05:11.203000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": ["845527584157597716"], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": "1420861801024852121", "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1420653274415235094", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "Tier List & Banner Guide", "forum_channel_id": "1304022827824844842", "thread_tags": ["1395992270880243753", "1304022948000043028"]}
{"id": "1420865895592493258", "channel_id": "1420653274415235094", "type": 19, "author_id": "845527584157597716", "author_name": "lurenjiao", "author_bot": false, "content": "After entering extra turns, you can play multiple Distant Melo cards, and since the Red Tentacle naturally comes with a 1.25 multiplier, the Crit Damage payoff is quite significant. At present, her strong niches are limited to these two teams; in other teams, she mostly fills a defensive role, as her defense can trigger twice.", "timestamp": "2025-09-25T20:13:47.921000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": ["244028747999608832"], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": "1420863728319987924", "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1420653274415235094", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "Tier List & Banner Guide", "forum_channel_id": "1304022827824844842", "thread_tags": ["1395992270880243753", "1304022948000043028"]}
